
[Boston, 1 July 1784. Entry in SJL reads: P. Mazzei. That Bowdoins conversion of a sterlg. into currency debt was illegalthat Jeffersons bond for 14646 and Gillespys & Hendersons for 100 having been so long kept by Bowdoin would be considered as a money paimentthat the former was my brothers affairreferred to N. Lewis and Key for papers and Garth for information. Not found.]
